Rewrite the regex to avoid catastrophic backtracking:
```javascript
// Instead of:
const regex = /(a+)+$/;  // Vulnerable!

// Use:
const regex = /a+$/;  // Non-nested quantifier

// Or use possessive quantifiers (if supported):
// Or add input length limits before regex matching:
if (input.length > 1000) throw new Error('Input too long');
```

